---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Boss PDX — Lucas Sommer" description="Licensed Portland general contractor with 17+ years of experience. Residential and commercial construction, ADU specialist, custom homes, excavation, and concrete work.">

  <article class="project-detail container">

    <a href="/projects" class="back-link">&larr; All Projects</a>

    <div class="project-hero">
      <div class="project-icon-lg" style="background:var(--status-exploring-bg); color:var(--status-exploring-text);">BP</div>
      <div>
        <h1>Boss PDX</h1>
        <span class="project-status status-active">Active</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="project-lede">
      Licensed Portland general contractor and construction expert. 17+ years building and remodeling homes and commercial properties across the Portland metro area. On time. On budget.
    </p>

    <div class="project-tags-lg">
      <span class="tag">Construction</span>
      <span class="tag">Portland</span>
      <span class="tag">General Contractor</span>
      <span class="tag">CCB #232383</span>
      <span class="tag">bosspdx.com</span>
    </div>

    <div class="detail-grid">

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>What is Boss PDX?</h2>
        <p>Boss PDX is a locally owned and operated construction company that's been building and remodeling homes and commercial properties across Portland for nearly two decades. From entire gut renovations of residential homes to building commercial properties to landscaping projects — the scope of work is extensive and diverse.</p>
        <p>What makes Boss PDX different is the technology layer. The company runs on Zoho for project management, Gusto for payroll, and Ramp for expense tracking — with AI-assisted estimating, an online customer portal, and structured post-mortems on every completed project.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Services</h2>
        <div class="services-grid">
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Custom Home Building</h3>
            <p>Full design-to-build for new residential construction. 35 years of combined experience bringing dream homes to life from concept to completion.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>ADU Specialist</h3>
            <p>Turn your basement, garage, or detached structure into a legally permitted ADU. Attached, detached, basement, and garage conversions — fully compliant with Portland zoning.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Commercial Concrete</h3>
            <p>Foundation work, slab-on-grade installations, large-scale infrastructure, and site development. Expert solutions for commercial properties throughout Portland.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Excavating</h3>
            <p>Land clearing and grading, foundation and utility excavation, drainage systems, and trenching. Creating safe, stable bases for construction.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Retaining Walls</h3>
            <p>Installation and repair to manage slopes, prevent erosion, and add structural interest to residential and commercial landscapes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Hardscaping</h3>
            <p>Custom hardscape features, pavers, walkways, patios, and outdoor living spaces for residential gardens and commercial landscapes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Exterior Work</h3>
            <p>Siding replacement, trim work, window and door replacement, roofing repairs, and complete exterior renovations.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Metal Buildings</h3>
            <p>Commercial storage, residential garages, agricultural buildings, workshops, retail spaces, and industrial facilities.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Commercial Remodeling</h3>
            <p>Tenant improvements, retail buildouts, office renovations, and commercial bathroom remodels.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Home Additions</h3>
            <p>Seamless room additions to multi-story extensions. Enhance living spaces and increase property value.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Kitchen & Bath</h3>
            <p>Full gut renovations or cosmetic updates. Cabinetry, countertops, backsplash, hardware sourcing, and complete design.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3>Pole Barns</h3>
            <p>Agricultural, commercial, and residential pole barn construction. Custom designs for storage, workshops, and more.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top:1rem;">Also: custom cabinetry & carpentry, masonry & stonework, drywall, painting, flooring, plumbing, garages, basement finishing, demolition, and construction permit management.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Service Areas</h2>
        <p>Downtown Portland, Lake Oswego, West Linn, Wilsonville, Tualatin, Tigard, Sherwood, Newberg, McMinnville, and Lincoln City.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>The Tech Stack</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Project management</strong> — Zoho Projects with automated flows for billing, scheduling, and client communication</li>
          <li><strong>AI-assisted estimating</strong> — Custom prompts that generate estimates from project parameters, dramatically reducing turnaround time</li>
          <li><strong>Customer portal</strong> — estimate.bosspdx.com where clients view estimates, project images, and 3D Polycam scans</li>
          <li><strong>Permit-ready plans</strong> — plans.bosspdx.com generates full construction submittals (cover sheet through structural calcs) from a structured project spec — architectural set, engineering set, or the full package</li>
          <li><strong>Post-mortem system</strong> — Every completed project gets a structured review: scope, budget vs actual, timeline, change orders, subcontractor performance, lessons learned</li>
          <li><strong>Crew operations</strong> — Gusto payroll mapped to projects, Ramp cards per project for real-time expense tracking</li>
          <li><strong>Subcontractor management</strong> — All subcontractor paperwork handled in-house with 15-20% markup for timeline and invoice management</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Notable Projects</h2>
        <p>Active and completed projects across Portland: Dilla, Bowden, Timberline, Kirkland, Archer, King, Joe Terrace, WaCo, Camus (Kirkland concrete), Bransford, and more. Each one feeds data back into the system — post-mortems, budget analysis, and operational learnings — to make the next project smoother.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>The Vision</h2>
        <p>Build the most data-driven construction company in Portland. Every project generates intelligence that makes the next one faster, more accurate, and more profitable. The tech stack isn't overhead — it's a competitive advantage. When your estimating is AI-powered and every past project is structured data, you can bid faster, scope tighter, and deliver better than anyone operating on spreadsheets and gut feel.</p>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="updates-section">
      <h2>Updates</h2>
      <div class="update-item">
        <div class="update-date">May 2026</div>
        <div class="update-title">Framing Engine v0.6 — vicinity maps + cleaner sheet sets</div>
        <div class="update-body">The plan generator now separates architectural and engineering sheets cleanly and adds vicinity maps. Permit submittals come out tighter and faster.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="update-item">
        <div class="update-date">May 2026</div>
        <div class="update-title">Architecture vs. engineering as a first-class mode</div>
        <div class="update-body">Generate an architectural set, an engineering set, or the full package from the same source spec — no rework, no duplicate drafting.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="update-item">
        <div class="update-date">May 2026</div>
        <div class="update-title">Plans by Boss PDX went live</div>
        <div class="update-body">The Framing Engine became a product at plans.bosspdx.com — a structured spec in, a permit-ready submittal out (cover sheet through structural calcs). First public project has already shipped through it.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── Videos (Boss PDX YouTube) ─────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="yt-section">
      <div class="yt-head">
        <h2>Watch</h2>
        <a class="yt-sub" href="https://www.youtube.com/@bosspdx1189" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube · @bosspdx1189 →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="yt-grid">
        <div class="yt-card">
          <iframe loading="lazy" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/NmAe2hbipn4" title="Residential Concrete Services in Portland" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="email-capture">
      <h3>Get a Free Estimate</h3>
      <p class="capture-sub">Planning a project in the Portland metro area? Get a free estimate or follow along as we build the most data-driven construction company in the Portland metro.</p>
      <form class="email-form">
        <input type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required />
        <button type="submit">Get updates</button>
      </form>
    </div>

    <!-- Related Projects -->
    <div class="related-projects">
      <h2>Related Projects</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/projects/ad-apt" class="related-card">
          <div class="related-icon" style="background:rgba(124,58,237,0.12); color:#a78bfa;">Aa</div>
          <div><div class="related-name">Ad-Apt</div><div class="related-desc">The marketing agency that grew Boss PDX from $0 to $1M</div></div>
        </a>
        <a href="/projects/grove-vineyard" class="related-card">
          <div class="related-icon" style="background:var(--status-active-bg); color:var(--status-active-text);">GV</div>
          <div><div class="related-name">Grove Vineyard</div><div class="related-desc">Another asset — vineyard in the Willamette Valley</div></div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </article>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  @import '../../styles/project-detail.css';

  .services-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .service-card {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1rem;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .service-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
  }

  .service-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .service-card p {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .services-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .services-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  /* ── YouTube videos section ───────────────────────────────────────── */
  .yt-section { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .yt-head {
    display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .yt-head h2 { font-size: 1.125rem; margin: 0; }
  .yt-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent-text);
  }
  .yt-grid {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .yt-card {
    position: relative; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    background: var(--surface-1); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden;
  }
  .yt-card iframe { position: absolute; inset: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: 0; }
</style>
